author: susantha
msg: Changes/Improvements for Doc/Literal style web services. Axis C++ will support
both Rpc/Encoded and Doc/Literal style services. These changes include,
1. Deserializer code changes to support multiple input buffers (chuncked data).
2. Deserializer API changes to support Doc/Lit as well
3. Ability to plugin other XML parsers (Xerces, Libxml, etc). But wrappers for other
parsers than Expat has to be written.
4. Fix of Compiler dependancy when supporting complete C web services
